comment.text:
Implemented with two overloads:
{code}
Container.Register(Component.For<Foo>()
                     .DependsOn(Dependency.OnResource<Resources>("foo", "SomeResource"),
                                Dependency.OnResource("arg1", Resources.ResourceManager, "SomeResource")));
{code}

The first one just specifies the autogenerated {{Resources}} class.

This will usually not work with Silverlight (the class is internal). To handle that, and also cases where we have resources without autogenerated class, we have another overload that takes an instance of {{ResourceManager}}.
